        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): render progress draft rows as plain readable text",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #95002.\n\nTelegram progress draft previews now keep their canonical preview text plain and readable instead of making ordinary tool/progress rows depend on Telegram HTML/code wrappers.\n\nBefore this change, progress drafts asserted payloads like:\n\n```html\n<b>Shelling</b><br><b>🛠️ Exec</b> <code>command false</code> <i>exit 2</i>\n```\n\nAfter this change, the same draft is represented as readable plain text:\n\n```text\nShelling\n\n🛠️ exit 2; command false\n```\n\n## Problem\n\nThe Telegram progress draft renderer used `<b>`, `<code>`, `<i>`, and `<br>` for transient progress rows. This made command/tool progress noisy even when HTML parsed successfully, and any fallback/sanitized rendering could expose transport markup to the user instead of a useful status line.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Stop wrapping Telegram progress draft lines in Markdown backticks/code spans.\n- Normalize Telegram progress draft rows to plain readable text first.\n- Keep non-rich Telegram progress drafts as plain text payloads instead of `parseMode: \"HTML\"` payloads.\n- Preserve rich-message support by continuing to build escaped HTML from the same normalized plain line model when rich messages are enabled.\n- Update Telegram dispatch tests to assert readable progress draft text instead of HTML/code payloads.\n\n## Verification\n\nLocal targeted checks:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts telegram/src/draft-stream.test.ts telegram/src/lane-delivery.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nResults:\n\n- `telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts`: 129 passed\n- `telegram/src/draft-stream.test.ts`: 46 passed\n- `telegram/src/lane-delivery.test.ts`: 41 passed\n- `git diff --check`: passed\n\n## Risk\n\nLow-to-moderate Telegram presentation risk:\n\n- This intentionally changes Telegram progress draft preview text from HTML-formatted rows to plain readable rows.\n- Final answer rendering is not changed.\n- Normal Telegram markdown/HTML answer rendering remains outside this progress-draft path.\n- Rich progress previews still get escaped HTML generated from the normalized plain line model.\n\n## Not addressed\n\nThis PR does not change Telegram draft materialization policy, including first-preview debounce/minimum length or progress-mode answer-lane suppression. That separate behavior is tracked in #95004 because it involves a product tradeoff between notification noise and Web preview parity.\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Telegram progress draft preview rows no longer expose HTML/code-style transport formatting for ordinary tool progress. The after-fix preview text is readable plain status text.\n- **Real environment tested:** Linux local OpenClaw checkout on this PR head.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** Ran the patched Telegram progress-preview path locally and captured the resulting preview payload text for the issue examples.\n- **Evidence after fix:** Copied terminal output from the patched local checkout:\n\n```text\nafter-fix Telegram progress preview payload:\nShelling\n\n🛠️ exit 2; command false\n\nAfter-fix non-command progress preview payload:\nShelling\n\n🔎 Web Search: docs lookup\n• tests passed\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The preview payload contains readable progress lines and no `<b>`, `<code>`, `<i>`, or `<br>` transport markup in the non-rich Telegram draft text path.\n- **What was not tested:** Live Bot API delivery in a public chat was not exercised for this formatting-only patch; final answer rendering is outside the changed progress-draft path.",
